    approach: "- Build a prefix-sum array `pre` of size `n+1` where `pre[i]` holds the sum of the first `i` elements (`pre[0] = 0`).\n- For a query `[left, right]`, the answer is `pre[right+1] - pre[left]`, since subtracting the prefix up to `left` cancels out everything before the window.\n- Construction is O(n) and each query is O(1), which is optimal for immutable arrays with many queries.",
    code: "#include <vector>\nusing namespace std;\n\nclass NumArray {\npublic:\n    // pre[i] = sum of nums[0..i-1]; pre[0] = 0 as sentinel\n    vector<int> pre;\n\n    NumArray(vector<int>& nums) {\n        int n = nums.size();\n        pre.resize(n + 1, 0);\n        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)\n            pre[i + 1] = pre[i] + nums[i];\n    }\n\n    // Sum of nums[left..right] = prefix up to right+1 minus prefix up to left\n    int sumRange(int left, int right) {\n        return pre[right + 1] - pre[left];\n    }\n};",
